<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="7308">
This species is known from Colchis, Georgian and Russian parts of the western Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, S. I." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="7308" pagination="887 - 915" title="Review of the millipede genus Hyleoglomeris Verhoeff, 1910 (Diplopoda, Glomerida, Glomeridae), with descriptions of new species from caves in Southeast Asia" volume="28" year="2006">Golovatch et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
). In the study area the animals were found in leaf litter, upper soil layers and under fallen twigs.
</paragraph>
